wikipedia_page.main: Sir John Claud Fortescue Fryer KBE FRS FRSE (13 August 1886 – 22 November 1948) was an English entomologist. He was president of the Royal Entomological Society from 1938 to 1939 and was a fellow of the Royal Society.

Amerila aldabrensis is a moth of the subfamily Arctiinae. It was described by John Fryer in 1912. It is found in the Seychelles.
Eilema contorta is a moth of the subfamily Arctiinae. It was described by John Fryer in 1912. It is found on the Seychelles.
Diptychophora muscella is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by John Fryer in 1912. It is found on the Seychelles, where it has been recorded from Mahé and Silhouette.
Glaucocharis muscela is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by John Fryer in 1912. It is found in the Seychelles.
